From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: VyOS LS1046A CI <ci@vyos-ls1046a>
Date: Thu, 29 May 2026 04:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] dpaa1: M3-3 step 7 sub-increment 1 - true-ZC RX eligibility
 probe (xsk_zc_eligible counter)

M3-3 step 7 (true zero-copy RX, spec sec 6.1.7 mechanism 1) is the only
unblocked kernel-code milestone remaining after the M3-3b/c/d struct
contracts landed and gate 3 was shown methodology-bound (sec 6.1.8a/b).
Productive true-ZC has three mechanisms (sec 6.1.7 lines "Recognise /
Recover / Program"): (1) recognise XSK-pool-sourced FDs by matching
fd->bpid against priv->xsk_bpid[band]; (2) recover the xdp_buff from the
XSK chunk; (3) reprogram the FMan RX port's primary BPID to the XSK pool.
Mechanism 3 is hardware-risky (the sec 6.1.8 history records three DUT
crashes from under-load XSK RX work). Following the de-risking cadence
that landed 0083 (observational xsk_rx_branch) before 0084's productive
branch, this sub-increment lands ONLY mechanism 1's recognition test as a
strictly-diagnostic counter, with zero datapath change.

A 17th xsk_* counter, xsk_zc_eligible, is bumped inside the existing 0083
RCU read-section in rx_default_dqrr() whenever an FD reaches a qband with
a bound XSK pool AND fd->bpid equals priv->xsk_bpid[band]. On the default
flavor no XSK pool is ever bound and xsk_bpid stays 0 while a live FD
always carries a non-zero kernel BPID, so the test never fires and packet
handling is byte-identical to mainline. Once sub-increment 2 reprograms
the FMan RX port BPID, this counter will track FDs that FMan DMA'd
directly into XSK-pool BMan chunks - proving the recognition arithmetic
before the risky reprogram is wired into the datapath.

Three edits, all additive:
  - dpaa_eth.h:    u64 xsk_zc_eligible; appended to the xsk_* counter block
  - dpaa_ethtool.c: "xsk_zc_eligible" appended to dpaa_stats_xsk[]
                    (value-emit loop is length-driven, no change needed)
  - dpaa_eth.c:    bpid-match test added inside the 0083 _xp != NULL arm

Signed-off-by: VyOS LS1046A CI <ci@vyos-ls1046a>
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
@@ -2851,8 +2851,20 @@
 
 		rcu_read_lock();
 		_xp = rcu_dereference(priv->xsk_pool[_band]);
-		if (_xp)
+		if (_xp) {
 			priv->xsk_rx_branch++;
+			/* M3-3 step 7 sub-increment 1 (patch 0093): the FD
+			 * reached a qband with a bound XSK pool. If FMan also
+			 * DMA'd it into an XSK-pool BMan chunk, fd->bpid equals
+			 * the dedicated BPID recorded by xsk_pool_attach().
+			 * Until sub-increment 2 reprograms the FMan RX port's
+			 * primary BPID, fd->bpid stays the kernel page BPID and
+			 * this stays 0 -- proving the recognition path is sound
+			 * with zero datapath risk. Spec sec 6.1.7 / 6.1.10.
+			 */
+			if (fd->bpid == priv->xsk_bpid[_band])
+				priv->xsk_zc_eligible++;
+		}
 		rcu_read_unlock();
 	}
 
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.h
@@ -288,6 +288,22 @@
  */
 u64 xsk_tx_conf_zc;
 
+/* M3-3 step 7 sub-increment 1 (patch 0093): observational
+ * true-ZC RX eligibility probe. Bumped in rx_default_dqrr()
+ * when an FD's bpid equals priv->xsk_bpid[band] for a band
+ * with a bound XSK pool -- i.e. the FD was DMA'd by FMan into
+ * an XSK-pool BMan chunk rather than a kernel page. Strictly
+ * diagnostic, mirroring xsk_rx_branch (0083): it proves the
+ * FD-recognition arithmetic (fd->bpid vs xsk_bpid[band]) is
+ * correct BEFORE the hardware-risky sub-increment 2 reprograms
+ * the FMan RX port's primary BPID to the XSK pool. With no XSK
+ * pool bound (default flavor) xsk_bpid stays 0 while a live FD
+ * always carries a non-zero kernel BPID, so this never fires
+ * and packet handling is byte-identical to mainline. Spec sec
+ * 6.1.7 true-ZC mechanism 1 + sec 6.1.10.
+ */
+u64 xsk_zc_eligible;
+
 /* M3-3b (patch 0086): FMan PCD capability bitmask snapshot taken
  * at probe via dpaa_fman_get_caps(). 0 on mainline ucode 106 ->
  * all fman_cc_tree_/fman_hm_/fman_pol_ helpers short-circuit
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_ethtool.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_ethtool.c
@@ -71,6 +71,7 @@
 "xsk_bman_refill_batches",
 "xsk_tx_zc_submit",
 "xsk_tx_conf_zc",
+"xsk_zc_eligible",
 };
 
 /* HW-offload (PCD-cap) counters (M3-3b / patch 0086). Order MUST match
